    },
    {
      "start": 421.84000000000003,
      "end": 424.68,
      "text": " Why would a big company mess around with something small?"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.68,
      "end": 429.48,
      "text": " But like John Thorne, Philip Knight and Bill Bowerman, when they founded Nike, a company"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.6,
      "end": 434.48,
      "text": " we all know very well today, had identified a problem, but it was a problem that a very"
    },
    {
      "start": 434.48,
      "end": 436.6,
      "text": " narrow target market had."
    },
    {
      "start": 436.6,
      "end": 440.72,
      "text": " Phil Knight was a runner, a distance runner, and he could run almost not quite a four-minute"
    },
    {
      "start": 440.72,
      "end": 444.6,
      "text": " mile, and Bill Bowerman was his track coach."
    },
    {
      "start": 444.6,
      "end": 448.68,
      "text": " And there's a problem with their shoes, because running shoes in those days were really made"
    },
    {
      "start": 448.68,
      "end": 449.68,
      "text": " for sprinters."
    },
    {
      "start": 449.68,
      "end": 452.72,
      "text": " And when sprinters train, they run around a track."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.72,
      "end": 454.52000000000004,
      "text": " It's a nice, smooth track."
    },
    {
      "start": 454.52000000000004,
      "end": 456.64000000000004,
      "text": " But distance runners don't run around tracks."
    },
    {
      "start": 456.64000000000004,
      "end": 457.8,
      "text": " Where do they run?"
    },
    {
      "start": 457.8,
      "end": 463.12,
      "text": " They run on country paths and dirt roads, and they're always stepping on sticks and rocks."
    },
    {
      "start": 463.12,
      "end": 467.56,
      "text": " And so they get sprained ankles, and they run mile after mile after mile, and they get"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.56,
      "end": 469.12,
      "text": " shin splints."
    },
    {
      "start": 469.12,
      "end": 474.8,
      "text": " Well Knight and Bowerman said, we need better shoes, shoes that are made especially for"
    },
    {
      "start": 474.8,
      "end": 480.2,
      "text": " distance runners, especially elite distance runners who really train a whole lot."
    },
    {
      "start": 480.2,
      "end": 485.12,
      "text": " So we're going to build a better shoe that's going to have better lateral stability, a wider"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.12,
      "end": 486.72,
      "text": " footbed."
    },
    {
      "start": 486.72,
      "end": 490.64000000000004,
      "text": " It's going to have a little more cushioning in it to protect against those shin splints."
    },
    {
      "start": 490.64000000000004,
      "end": 495.08000000000004,
      "text": " And by the way, if it's a little bit lighter weight, a few ounces lighter times all the"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.08000000000004,
      "end": 499.44000000000005,
      "text": " steps in running a mile or a two mile or a marathon, it's going to make for faster"
    },
    {
      "start": 499.44000000000005,
      "end": 501.64000000000004,
      "text": " race times too."
    },
    {
      "start": 501.64000000000004,
      "end": 504.64000000000004,
      "text": " So we know what happened with Nike, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 504.64000000000004,
      "end": 511.36,
      "text": " Once they developed the skills to design shoes explicitly made for a target market, a narrow"
    },
    {
      "start": 511.36,
      "end": 512.36,
      "text": " one."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.36,
      "end": 516.7,
      "text": " And once they learned to import those shoes from Asia, and once they learned to get athlete"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.0600000000001,
      "end": 519.1800000000001,
      "text": " to adopt those shoes, what did they do?"
    },
    {
      "start": 519.1800000000001,
      "end": 524.3000000000001,
      "text": " Well John McEnroe and Tennis, Michael Jordan and Basketball came next, and we know what"
    },
    {
      "start": 524.3000000000001,
      "end": 525.9000000000001,
      "text": " the story is with Nike today."
    },
    {
      "start": 525.9000000000001,
      "end": 530.22,
      "text": " They're the global leader in athletic footwear and much more."
    },
    {
      "start": 530.22,
      "end": 532.1800000000001,
      "text": " Okay, the next one."
    },
    {
      "start": 532.1800000000001,
      "end": 534.86,
      "text": " Asking for the cash and riding the float."
    },
    {
      "start": 534.86,
      "end": 538.22,
      "text": " Big companies today are awash in cash."
    },
    {
      "start": 538.22,
      "end": 542.5400000000001,
      "text": " Even in these tricky times we're in today, there's cash all over the place, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 542.54,
      "end": 549.78,
      "text": " Burke in 2018 spent all this money giving money back to shareholders through stock buybacks"
    },
    {
      "start": 549.78,
      "end": 555.5799999999999,
      "text": " and dividends, and they could only find 10 billion worth of R&D to do with all that cash."
    },
    {
      "start": 555.5799999999999,
      "end": 556.5799999999999,
      "text": " Is something wrong here?"
    },
    {
      "start": 556.5799999999999,
      "end": 559.54,
      "text": " I think this just doesn't feel right."
    },
    {
      "start": 559.54,
      "end": 565.54,
      "text": " But for entrepreneurs like Elon Musk and the Tesla team, cash is the lifeblood of the entrepreneurial"
    },
    {
      "start": 565.54,
      "end": 566.54,
      "text": " venture."
    },
    {
      "start": 566.54,
      "end": 570.18,
      "text": " So when Musk joined the Tesla team, he said, well, what's the plan here?"
    },
    {
      "start": 570.18,
      "end": 571.18,
      "text": " And the team had a plan."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.18,
      "end": 575.9399999999999,
      "text": " It was to build a really fancy sports car, make a lot of money from that one, use that"
    },
    {
      "start": 575.9399999999999,
      "end": 580.3399999999999,
      "text": " money to build a somewhat lower price car, make some money from that one, and then we're"
    },
    {
      "start": 580.3399999999999,
      "end": 584.9,
      "text": " going to build a mass market car that more people can afford."
    },
    {
      "start": 584.9,
      "end": 590.26,
      "text": " And in so doing, we're going to make a real dent in the emissions problem that the global"
    },
    {
      "start": 590.26,
      "end": 593.5,
      "text": " automobile industry creates."
    },
    {
      "start": 593.5,
      "end": 598.62,
      "text": " Well what Musk said is, well, let's go see if we can sell some cars."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.62,
      "end": 604.18,
      "text": " So they did a little road show in California, and they invited people on this little road"
    },
    {
      "start": 604.18,
      "end": 606.54,
      "text": " show with three characteristics."
    },
    {
      "start": 606.54,
      "end": 609.14,
      "text": " Number one, they cared about the environment."
    },
    {
      "start": 609.14,
      "end": 611.5,
      "text": " Number two, they were wealthy."
    },
    {
      "start": 611.5,
      "end": 614.94,
      "text": " Number three, they thought it might be cool to have the next big thing parked in their"
    },
    {
      "start": 614.94,
      "end": 615.94,
      "text": " driveway."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.94,
      "end": 617.82,
      "text": " Well, guess what?"
    },
    {
      "start": 617.82,
      "end": 625.94,
      "text": " They sold 100 Tesla roadsters for $100,000 each, cash on the barrelhead, paid tonight."
    },
    {
      "start": 625.94,
      "end": 627.78,
      "text": " How much do the math?"
    },
    {
      "start": 627.78,
      "end": 630.5,
      "text": " How much money they got to start building roadsters?"
    },
    {
      "start": 630.5,
      "end": 636.3,
      "text": " $10 million in the bank in cash before they had built roadster number one."
    },
    {
      "start": 636.3,
      "end": 640.6999999999999,
      "text": " Well that principle has carried Tesla all the way through its journey."
    },
    {
      "start": 640.6999999999999,
      "end": 646.9399999999999,
      "text": " So when they introduced the Model 3 several years ago, nearly half a million consumers"
    },
    {
      "start": 646.9399999999999,
      "end": 650.42,
      "text": " put down deposits of $1,000 each."
    },
    {
      "start": 650.42,
      "end": 657.06,
      "text": " Do that math, half a million consumers, $1,000 each, half a billion dollars in the bank in"
    },
    {
      "start": 657.06,
      "end": 662.02,
      "text": " cash with which to begin doing the engineering, build the tooling, fit out the factory and"
    },
    {
      "start": 662.02,
      "end": 663.02,
      "text": " more."
    },
    {
      "start": 663.02,
      "end": 668.5799999999999,
      "text": " Wouldn't you like to build your entrepreneurial venture with that kind of business model?"
    },
    {
      "start": 668.5799999999999,
      "end": 669.9799999999999,
      "text": " Okay, the next one."
    },
    {
      "start": 669.9799999999999,
      "end": 673.5,
      "text": " I call it bag borrow, but please, please don't steal."
    },
    {
      "start": 673.5,
      "end": 679.2199999999999,
      "text": " In B-School Finance, we teach our students how to analyze whether a project's any good."
    },
    {
      "start": 679.2199999999999,
      "end": 683.18,
      "text": " So you figure out how much investment you have to do, and then you figure out what the cash"
    },
    {
      "start": 683.18,
      "end": 687.26,
      "text": " flows are going to be going forward year after year after year for five years or ten"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.26,
      "end": 688.5799999999999,
      "text": " years or whatever."
    },
    {
      "start": 688.5799999999999,
      "end": 694.14,
      "text": " And then you ask yourself, well is that return on that investment sufficient?"
    },
    {
      "start": 694.14,
      "end": 697.18,
      "text": " And if the ROI is good enough, then you do the project."
    },
    {
      "start": 697.18,
      "end": 698.5,
      "text": " That's the idea."
    },
    {
      "start": 698.5,
      "end": 704.9799999999999,
      "text": " But for Tristram Mayhew and Rebecca Mayhew, his wife, who built a wonderful business in"
    },
    {
      "start": 704.9799999999999,
      "end": 710.78,
      "text": " the UK called Go Ape, a treetop adventure business, they didn't think that way at all."
    },
    {
      "start": 710.78,
      "end": 715.4599999999999,
      "text": " They said, well we want to build a treetop adventure business here in the UK."
    },
    {
      "start": 715.4599999999999,
      "end": 718.78,
      "text": " They'd seen one in France that they liked on a vacation."
    },
    {
      "start": 718.78,
      "end": 721.02,
      "text": " So where can we get some trees?"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.02,
      "end": 724.5,
      "text": " Well who's got trees in the UK?"
    },
    {
      "start": 724.5,
      "end": 729.74,
      "text": " Well turns out the UK Forestry Commission has trees in the UK, lots of them, in all these"
    },
    {
      "start": 729.74,
      "end": 731.54,
      "text": " Forestry Commission sites."
    },
    {
      "start": 731.54,
      "end": 736.02,
      "text": " And the Forestry Commission was very interested in increasing their visitor count."
    },
    {
      "start": 736.02,
      "end": 741.62,
      "text": " Well what better way to increase their visitor count than to have a Go Ape treetop adventure"
    },
    {
      "start": 741.62,
      "end": 744.24,
      "text": " course on their land?"
    },
    {
      "start": 744.24,
      "end": 749.38,
      "text": " So what Tristram Becks essentially did was go to the Forest Service and say look, or"
    },
    {
      "start": 749.38,
      "end": 754.9399999999999,
      "text": " the Forestry Commission and say look, if you'll give us a chance to build five of these and"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.9399999999999,
      "end": 759.98,
      "text": " show you that it works, we'd like an exclusive for the rest of them for 25 years."
    },
    {
      "start": 759.98,
      "end": 761.6999999999999,
      "text": " The deal was done."
    },
    {
      "start": 761.7,
      "end": 766.5,
      "text": " Today there are more than 30 Go Ape adventure sites across the UK."
    },
    {
      "start": 766.5,
      "end": 768.86,
      "text": " There are a whole bunch of them in the US."
    },
    {
      "start": 768.86,
      "end": 770.5,
      "text": " And how did that happen?"
    },
    {
      "start": 770.5,
      "end": 773.9000000000001,
      "text": " Because they borrowed most of the assets they needed."
    },
    {
      "start": 773.9000000000001,
      "end": 778.1,
      "text": " They borrowed the trees, they borrowed the lures, they borrowed the parking lots, all"
    },
    {
      "start": 778.1,
      "end": 781.7,
      "text": " that stuff, all they had to do was put their kid on the trees."
    },
    {
      "start": 781.7,
      "end": 782.7,
      "text": " Pretty cool."
    },
    {
      "start": 782.7,
      "end": 787.4200000000001,
      "text": " Now, entrepreneurs and permission are kind of like oil and water."
    },
    {
      "start": 787.4200000000001,
      "end": 790.32,
      "text": " If you're an entrepreneur you kind of know that, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 790.32,
      "end": 795.2800000000001,
      "text": " But in a big company today, if you want to get something new done, something entrepreneurial,"
    },
    {
      "start": 795.2800000000001,
      "end": 799.08,
      "text": " something that's maybe a little different than the norm, you've got to pass it through"
    },
    {
      "start": 799.08,
      "end": 803.48,
      "text": " the lawyers first because there are a lot of regulations everywhere and you don't want"
    },
    {
      "start": 803.48,
      "end": 806.82,
      "text": " to do something that's going to land a top exec in jail."
    },
    {
      "start": 806.82,
      "end": 810.9200000000001,
      "text": " So it's really hard to get a yes answer to doing something that's new and innovative"
    },
    {
      "start": 810.9200000000001,
      "end": 815.1600000000001,
      "text": " and it takes a long time, but it's really easy to get a no."
    },
    {
      "start": 815.16,
      "end": 821.12,
      "text": " For entrepreneurs, however, like Travis Kalanick and Garrett Camp who founded Uber, do you"
    },
    {
      "start": 821.12,
      "end": 826.3199999999999,
      "text": " think they would have been wise to ask the permission of the San Francisco regulators,"
    },
    {
      "start": 826.3199999999999,
      "end": 829.56,
      "text": " can we start a taxi company without any taxis?"
    },
    {
      "start": 829.56,
      "end": 831.4,
      "text": " No maybe not, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 831.4,
      "end": 835.48,
      "text": " Because had they asked, what do you think the regulators would have said?"
    },
    {
      "start": 835.48,
      "end": 837.04,
      "text": " There's no way you're going to do that."
    },
    {
      "start": 837.04,
      "end": 840.0,
      "text": " That's going to threaten the current taxi industry, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 840.0,
      "end": 843.88,
      "text": " So entrepreneurs don't ask permission, they just get on with it."
    },
    {
      "start": 843.88,
      "end": 849.72,
      "text": " Now I don't condone many of the things that Uber did along the journey, many of them unethical,"
    },
    {
      "start": 849.72,
      "end": 856.32,
      "text": " some of them probably illegal, but the principle of entrepreneurs just getting on with it when"
    },
    {
      "start": 856.32,
      "end": 863.64,
      "text": " the regulations are perhaps ambiguous or haven't sort of considered what could be done today"
    },
    {
      "start": 863.64,
      "end": 867.12,
      "text": " digitally, that's when you get on with it."
    },
    {
      "start": 867.12,
      "end": 872.6,
      "text": " Okay, so I want to close with four questions for you."
    },
    {
      "start": 872.6,
      "end": 878.2,
      "text": " Question number one, which of these mindsets are embodied in you today, maybe one or two"
    },
    {
      "start": 878.2,
      "end": 880.4,
      "text": " of them already?"
    },
    {
      "start": 880.4,
      "end": 883.24,
      "text": " Question number two, which of the others can you learn?"
    },
    {
      "start": 883.24,
      "end": 884.44,
      "text": " Are these learnable?"
    },
    {
      "start": 884.44,
      "end": 886.36,
      "text": " I think they are."
    },
    {
      "start": 886.36,
      "end": 892.32,
      "text": " Question number three, can you teach these to somebody you work with who has some challenges"
    },
    {
      "start": 892.32,
      "end": 894.84,
      "text": " for which these mindsets might help?"
    },
    {
      "start": 894.84,
      "end": 901.24,
      "text": " And more pertinently today, is there a challenge you face today for which one of these mindsets"
    },
    {
      "start": 901.24,
      "end": 906.96,
      "text": " or a couple of them might help you get beyond the roadblocks you're facing with that challenge?"
    },
    {
      "start": 906.96,
      "end": 909.48,
      "text": " Okay, so there we go."
    },
    {
      "start": 909.48,
      "end": 917.64,
      "text": " Six, counter-conventional, break the rules mindsets that can help anyone, maybe you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 917.64,
      "end": 918.16,
      "text": " change the world."
    }
  ]
}